title: Drawing, "End Table, Round", 1933
medium: Graphite on tracing paper, ruled border in graphite
markings: Stamp in black ink at lower right: DONALD DESKEY/ 145 WEST 57TH STREET/ NEW YORK CITY
inscribed: Inscribed in graphite at lower left: BL - S - W./ 9/1/33; lower left corner: 6; lower right: SCALE 1 1/2"=1'0"/7197 [circled]; lower right corner in red color pencil: P; dimensions in graphite
description: Perspective, plan, and elevation drawing of low, round end table in wood or Bakelite (?). Circular top with narrow, planar base; open shelf at center and two semi-circular shelves on each side; small drawer below shelves, and larger open shelf below. Circular base probably Bakelite.
